HEADWORD: cyclide
<hw>cy"clide</hw> <pr>(s?"kl?d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ky`klos</grk> circle.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A surface of
the fourth degree, having certain special relations to spherical
surfaces. The tore or anchor ring is one of the cyclides.</def>⟦br⟧
